      "abstract": "<ns3:p>Under the umbrella of covid19.galaxyproject.org many members of the Galaxy community have been working together since February 2020 to provide workflows, data sources and best-practice recommendations for SARS-CoV-2-related data analysis. In particular, the subproject of sequencing data analysis has undergone substantial transformation since the early phase of the pandemic. What started out as a collection of workflows for the assembly of early WGS data into reference genomes, for phylogenetic analysis to put a date on the emergence of Covid-19 and for variant calling from relatively few WGS datasets, has developed into a complete system capable of supporting global genome surveillance efforts and involving collaborations and public infrastructure across many countries. Here, we will present the current status of our efforts and how it aims at bringing Galaxy's key features, reproducibility and accessibility, to public health systems.</ns3:p>",
